# Fluff Date: 2026-03-09 16:42:39
<overview>
<p>The Morrígú is an 80-ton tracked fire support vehicle introduced in 3064 by Clan Blood Spirit. Khan Karianna Schmitt commissioned the design in the aftermath of the Absorption War, intending it to stand alongside new developments in the Blood Spirit OmniMech and ProtoMech programs as a demonstration of the Clan's continuing martial capability. The design reflects a century of Blood Spirit engineering philosophy: practical weapons without extravagant technologies, paired with more armor protection than is typically found on Clan combat vehicles of comparable size.</p><p>Khan Schmitt chose the vehicle's name personally, drawing on the Welsh ancestry revered within Blood Spirit culture to invoke a Celtic goddess of war, reinforcing the Clan's intention to remain a dangerous force. The Morrígú delivers concentrated long-range firepower from a well-protected hull, establishing a clear combat identity as a dedicated fire support platform.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Morrígú's primary armament consists of two Series 1 extended-range large lasers and two Type XV "Crossbow" LRM-15 launchers, all mounted in a turret for full traverse. This configuration delivers concentrated fire at extended range and reflects the Blood Spirits' long-standing preference for direct energy weapons, a philosophy evident across multiple Blood Spirit designs including the Blood Kite. Mounting all primary weapons in the turret allows the Morrígú to engage targets at any bearing without repositioning the hull, a useful capability given its limited ground speed.</p><p>For close defense, a Pattern J1 SRM-2 launcher is mounted on each flank, covering threats that close inside the main engagement envelope. A Consolidated Type 2M ECM suite adds electronic protection, complicating enemy targeting solutions. Both the communications and targeting systems are Consolidated products, providing reliable electronics performance.</p><p>The Morrígú carries thirteen tons of Compound JX4 armor, more substantial than most Clan combat vehicles at this weight class. However, the Fusion 240 powerplant produces a top speed of only 54 km/h, limiting tactical flexibility considerably. This vehicle is designed for static fire positions at range rather than mobile engagements. Commanders who rely on the Morrígú in fluid situations where the battle line shifts quickly will find its pace a genuine liability. It carries no jump jets, and repositioning under pressure offers no quick solution.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The HAG variant was developed at the New York Vehicle Y2 Facility on Trondheim and introduced in 3083, reflecting the Diamond Sharks' willingness to evolve the design beyond its Blood Spirit origins. The two ER large lasers are replaced with a single HAG/40, retained in the turret alongside the LRM-15s and SRM-2 flankers of the base vehicle. The hyper-assault Gauss rifle delivers exceptional damage in the medium-to-long range bracket and is particularly effective against massed or concentrated targets. The cost is increased dependence on ammunition supply, as the HAG/40 consumes significant stores in sustained engagements. This variant appeals most to forces with guaranteed resupply access seeking maximum burst damage rather than sustained energy fire. Production is exclusive to Trondheim; the original York facility never produced this configuration.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Morrígú was commissioned in the early 3060s by Khan Karianna Schmitt of Clan Blood Spirit, intended as a visible assertion of continued strength in the aftermath of the Absorption War. Alongside the Crimson Langur OmniMech and the ongoing ProtoMech development effort, the vehicle was one of several projects meant to signal that the Blood Spirits remained capable of fielding competitive military hardware.</p><p>Khan Schmitt chose the vehicle's name personally. Her Welsh heritage was held in near-sacred regard among the Blood Spirits, tracing lineage directly to Colleen Schmitt, the Clan's founding Khan. Colleen Schmitt had descended from Colonel Hanni Schmitt, the last commander of the Royal Black Watch Regiment of the Star League, a lineage treated as nearly holy within Blood Spirit culture. Drawing on that ancestry, Khan Karianna Schmitt chose a name from Celtic mythology: the Morrígú, a goddess of war said to appear wherever battle was joined. The name was a deliberate statement of purpose.</p><p>Production at the York Vehicle Y2 Facility on York began in 3064, and the vehicle was distributed across every Galaxy in the Blood Spirit Touman, including the newly established Iota Galaxy: Retribution. A complete Star of Morrígú vehicles appeared within the Twenty-second Combat Force, a Trinary formed by Kindraa Mick-Kreese of Clan Fire Mandrill, signaling the strengthening bond between the Blood Spirits and their Crusader-aligned neighbors in the Homeworlds. That the vehicle found favor with the most fanatically Crusader of the Kindraa factions was seen as fitting, given the Blood Spirits' own Crusader leanings.</p><p>The Wars of Reaving ultimately destroyed Clan Blood Spirit as a political entity. Before the York facility was lost, however, Clan Diamond Shark had acquired the production plans. In 3068 the Sharks established the New York Vehicle Y2 Facility on Trondheim, named explicitly in reference to its predecessor. Where the original production served the Blood Spirits exclusively, the Trondheim facility operated as a commercial venture, making the Morrígú available to any buyer. During the Jihad, the facility suffered significant personnel losses but maintained production at reduced capacity, and it carried the design forward through the Dark Age and into the ilClan era under Diamond Shark, and later Sea Fox, stewardship.</p>
</history>

